HEADWORD: Anoplotherium
<hw>An`o*plo*the"ri*um</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`⟦osl⟧*pl⟦osl⟧*th⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From Gr. <grk>'a`noplos</grk> unarmed (<grk>'an</grk> priv. +
<grk>'o`plon</grk> an implement, weapon) + <grk>qhri`on</grk>
beast.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of extinct quadrupeds of
the order <ord>Ungulata</ord>, whose were first found in the gypsum
quarries near Paris; characterized by the shortness and feebleness of
their canine teeth (whence the name).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anoplura</ent>⟦br⟧
